bug.short_desc: the ordering of voting categories is not consistent

long_desc.thetext:
While voting on an Eclipse.org Gerrit change I noticed that the order of voting categories in the Task Editor was as following:
IP Clean, Code Review, Verified
While the publish dialog displayed:
IP Clean, Verified, Code Review
The expected order (matching the web ui is):
Verified, Code Review, IP Clean
I also noticed that when I reopened the publish dialog the previous voting selections weren't active any longer resulting in a different vote I hit okay.
*** Bug 418945 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Thanks for looking into this. I'm not sure if we have enough information on the client side to sort the categories since users can define custom ones. Just from looking at the JSON briefly I'm wondering if we need to retain the order that was returned from the server: https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/17387/. Did you try that?

This makes sense, even though the REST API doc says nothing about the labels ordering [1]. I will verify if this is consistent between different versions and instance of Gerrit.
[1] https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/rest-api-changes.html#change-info
My assumption was also that we'd simply use the server provided (raw) ordering. That should carry through to the model.

Before resolving this bug I would like to consider the fix for inclusion for 3.10 and for a backport to 3.9.2:
https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/17387/
A related issue that we could consider tackling as part of this bug as well is the ordering of categories in the editor which is not consistent with the web UI.
